, where it is pronounced <i>bruff</i> or <i>broof</i> (/brʊf/). The Scottish surname was probably brought in from Yorkshire. For the surname in Ireland see   Burke  ."]}]},{"name":"Alicia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Alisha","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alisia","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alyssa","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alissa ."]},{"name":"Alissa","meanings":["Contracted form of   Alicia ."]},{"name":"Alesha","meanings":["Respelling of   Alicia ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":19,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":50,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Alicia Bury was born about 1240, in Lincolnshire, England. She had at least 1 son with John Otteby. She died about 1310, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 72."},"et":{"about 1240–about 1310":"umbes 1240–umbes 1310","1235–1280":"1235–1280","1260–1360":"1260–1360","1240–1310":"1240–1310","1259":"1259","1235":"1235","1310":"1310","about 1310":"umbes 1310","1240":"1240"